            "img": "cache_images/443829.jpg",
            "players": "2-8P",
            "weight": 1.0,
            "categories": [
                "Animals"
            ],
            "description": "In Wriggle Roulette, players take turns reaching into a bag filled with eel- and snake-shaped wooden pieces, trying to pull out as many eels as possible &mdash; but if the number of snakes grabbed by all players exceeds the limit, a \"snake outbreak\" occurs, and the player who grabbed the most pieces loses all of their eels.\n\nYou want to grab more than everyone else to score big, yet a snake outbreak would be devastating. Will you grab a bunch? Just a few? Or back out entirely? Read your opponents' expressions and control your own greed to make the right call.\n\n"
